import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x="region", y="income_per_capita", data=data)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of income per capita across all regions?", wrap=True)
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="region", y="income_per_capita", data=data, ci=None, estimator=sum)
    plt.title("What is the average income per capita for each region?", wrap=True)
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='income_per_capita', y='pct', hue='region')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between income per capita and percentage of population in each region?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='total', hue='region', multiple='stack', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['total'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['total'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['region', 'group']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="region", y="counts", hue="group", data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income groups across all regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
